> Is there a reason we don't read directly into the std::string?

@luke-jr If I am not wrong, it is not advisable to `fread` into `std::string` as `c_str()` is `const` and we will also need to know the size of the file beforehand to allocate the right number of characters. [More Details](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/13612340/c-fread-into-a-stdstring)

> Looks like your patch causes a "global buffer overflow" in the ASan CI task

@MarcoFalke fixed the ASan issue in the unit test.
